Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 9/18/2024

This Privacy Policy explains how Philip McLaughlin ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and retains your information when you use our app in connection with Instagram and Facebook analytics.

1. Introduction

We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This policy outlines the types of data we collect from Instagram and Facebook through the use of our app, how we use that data, and the measures we take to keep it secure.

2. Data We Collect

We collect the following types of data from Instagram and Facebook when you use our app:

Profile Information: This includes your Instagram profile name, profile picture, and other publicly available details from your profile.
Engagement Metrics: Data related to your interactions on Instagram and Facebook, such as likes, comments, shares, and followers.
Event Timing: We track timestamps related to specific interactions on Instagram and Facebook (e.g., when likes or comments occur).
3. How We Use the Data

The data we collect is solely used for analyzing engagement metrics on Instagram and Facebook. We do not share this information with any third parties. The data is retained for an indefinite period to allow for ongoing analytics.

4. Data Retention

We retain the collected data indefinitely unless you request its deletion. If you wish to request data deletion, you can contact us at philipthegingermclaughlin@gmail.com. While we will make reasonable efforts to comply with deletion requests, we cannot guarantee that data will be deleted immediately or in all cases.

5. User Rights and Data Deletion

You have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of the data we collect from you. To make such a request, please contact us at philipthegingermclaughlin@gmail.com. We will respond to your request as promptly as possible, but please note that delays may occur.

6. Security Measures

We implement standard security measures to protect the data we collect and maintain. However, no method of data transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

7. Changes to the Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time without prior notice. Any changes will be reflected in this document, and your continued use of the app following such updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.

8. Contact Information

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, you can contact us at:

Philip McLaughlin
Email: philipthegingermclaughlin@gmail.com
Instagram: @philipmakesstuff
